name: 李老师不是你老师
content:
Economist Lu Ting: It is not that developers built a lot of houses but did not sell them, but that they sold a lot of houses but did not finish building them. He pointed out that developers quickly recovered funds through a high turnover model, but passed on construction risks to home buyers. When the market is down and the capital chain is tight, "unfinished buildings" become a black hole that devours family wealth. 
This report has been deleted by major Chinese social media platforms. https://pbs.twimg.com/media/Gke__ZwaoAAkhwT.jpg

name: 李老师不是你老师
content: On February 23, a Hong Kong man reported that Gu Shuhua, the boss of Changzhou Sanwei Company in the mainland, had been manufacturing and selling fake drugs for 9 years. Gu Shuhua purchased L-carnitine, a chemical product with the same chemical structure as L-carnitine from Zhejiang, and made L-carnitine injection for sale, with the quantity reaching 20 million. 1.5 million renal dialysis patients used fake drugs made from chemical raw materials, and this unscrupulous incident was still concealed and protected by the black umbrella. https://pbs.twimg.com/ext_tw_video_thumb/1893697584193241088/pu/img/huVX370zOb-ScIrH.jpg

name: 李老师不是你老师
content:
"Brother Long", the person in charge of Beijing Mange Electric Auto Repair Shop, has been sued by the manufacturer again. On February 23, "Brother Long" received a complaint from a car manufacturer in Guangzhou, which demanded him to pay 1 million yuan in compensation and apologize.
"Brother Long" said that he has been sued by three new energy car companies. He made the video just to teach car owners how to save money and avoid pitfalls, but he didn't expect to help the legal department of the car company meet the target. I hope everyone will learn from it and stop saying negative news about some car companies. https://pbs.twimg.com/ext_tw_video_thumb/1893703719914790912/pu/img/vVRIyrvCkzNK8wF3.jpg

February 23, Anhui. A delivery rider fell off his bike and convulsed. https://pbs.twimg.com/ext_tw_video_thumb/1893742136891506688/pu/img/_ABV2GrAb5hNLIlJ.jpg

name: 李老师不是你老师
content: On February 23, the blogger interviewed a 67-year-old uncle. The uncle said that he worked as a construction worker outside, with a daily salary of about 150 yuan. He could not afford meat and usually ate steamed buns and porridge. The uncle lived in a house with a daily rent of 6 yuan. The house was built with wooden boards and the space was so small that it could only accommodate a bed. He said, "I have so much pain in my heart that I can't say it. I wish I could hit my head against my head and die. I have never enjoyed happiness in my life." https://pbs.twimg.com/ext_tw_video_thumb/1893890243201241088/pu/img/gqfOg0ELKt3QEFls.jpg

name: 李老师不是你老师
content:
On February 24, People's Daily: Why do we say "my country's demographic dividend is still continuing?": Annual consumption of middle-aged and elderly people in cultural tourism exceeds 700 billion yuan, the number of people in online education is about 35 million, and the number of marathon participants increases year by year... Sixty or seventy years old is the age to "break through".
Netizens said: "People are not dividends" "Your dividends, my blood and tears" https://pbs.twimg.com/media/GkinLvOaoAIF0ZJ.png

name: 李老师不是你老师
content: February 23 (Published) A blogger talks about the truth behind cheap Chinese cars: some domestic cars start to rust after only two or three years of purchase. Since the price war, the sheet metal of cars has become thinner and thinner. Some car companies use iron fuel tanks instead of high-pressure resin fuel tanks to save costs. https://pbs.twimg.com/ext_tw_video_thumb/1893951982831812608/pu/img/q-anMSMPrN6ipDgJ.jpg
